<I><font size="2">"If you are attacked on your style, never answer; your work alone should reply." -Voltaire</font></I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umajestykvz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MajestykVZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/1/00 2:02:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POLL: PvP Forum?</span><hr size=1> Shanks causing trouble?  I'm shocked!<br>
<br>
I hesitantly voted "Yes" on the 29th.  I hesitated due to the form of the question.  The Safehouse does not "Need" a PvP forum.  Those of us that engage in PvP can look for the info in the library or ask for information, just as we would on any other rogue related subject.  A new forum is not necessary.<br>
<br>
If the question had been "Should the SafeHouse have a PvP forum?", then I would vote "Yes" without hesitation.<br>
<br>
For me, EQ without PvP, is not worth playing.  There is too much whining, bitching, and generally rude behaviour, that occurs on the blue servers that does not occur to the same extent on the PvP servers due to the fact that players can have a direct impact on each others health bar.  Maybe it just seems to be less of an occurance to me due to the fact I'm not as frustrated by it, due to the fact I can have a direct impact on the offending players health bar.<br>
<br>
Whether you are on a blue or red server, there are enough differences between PvP and PvE combat and enough players that are interested in those differences, to warrant a forum dedicated to PvP play. <p>Majestyk, <a href="http://Server3.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse">Rogue</a>, <a href="http://galaxy.apropos.org/shanks">Shanks</a>, <a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/board.asp?brd=5034">Vallon Zek!</a>

