We as Shanks, have chosen the hard path. In the hardness of it, is where we find the glory.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/deleteThreadFire.gif width=0 height=0 border=0 BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/2/00 4:30:00 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.theglobe.com/kambic/trinity.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POLL: PvP Forum?</span><hr size=1> Well Kezzek already decided it would not be passworded. This is fine by me, because this is not rogue-specific. Just like the Back Alley is not rogue-specific and the By the Fireplace is not rogue-specific. Yes, it's designed for rogues, but not limited to them. PvP'ing against a rogue is not that hard, being one and knowing all his moves. Info from other classes would be very welcomed here, in my opinion.<br>
<br>
That said, I'd vouch for passworded also, as my own class secrets could be shared more freely :)<br>
<br>
Seriously though, how many non-rogues come here regularly? Meddik, Prenn (and retired at that), and who else? Cutlass Jack/Sabatini if you count him heh.<br>
