 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufricka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fricka</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.thegamevine.com/~Elegant_Rogue/shanks/teenyknot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/2/00 8:22:58 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/fricka_on_vallon_zek/fricka60x56.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POLL: PvP Forum?</span><hr size=1> Kambic you'd be surprised how many non-rogues come here. Note the influx of rogues who also have druids and other classes in their signature.  Many other classes lurk here.<br>
<br>
I was slain by a group of 3 casters and their pet while I was in South Karana one time.  One of them sent a tell to me, &quot;Look at the little girl with the pretty sig run.&quot;  ::chuckles:: It gave me a laugh.<br>
<br>
Of course I also laughed later as I slew their brethern and made off with their platinum.<br>
<br>
As an ezboard admin myself I know one can use the &quot;mimic forum&quot; function to copy the security options (this includes the list of people with access) from one forum to another.  However, I can see how that would place an added burden on the moderators since we are going through a lot with the Root Cellar. To update the access you would simply need to use the mimic function perhaps once a week?<br>
<br>
But, even if the forum is not passworded I think it will come in handy.  We have had several PvP questions come up recently and I've noticed that they are more regular in occurance as well.<br>
<br>
Oh, and Bluud's guide is indeed in the Library.  As well as on the Shanks site (since the &quot;Master Assassin&quot; himself was our founder).<br>
